    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-09-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-09-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="600"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d600">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <gloss target="#t_JCS1">J.C.S.</gloss> Files: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> and Prime
                        Minister <persName>Churchill</persName> to the Commander in Chief, Allied
                        Force Headquarters</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Eisenhower</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">operational priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-09-02">September 2,
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6704. From President Roosevelt and the Prime Minister to General Eisenhower,
                    personal and secret.</p>
                <p>Your <gloss target="#t_Naf1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Naf</hi>
                    </gloss> 346,<note n="1" xml:id="d600fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1257">p. 1257</ref>.</note>
                        347,<note n="2" xml:id="d600fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1259">p. 1259</ref>.</note>
                    and 348.<note n="3" xml:id="d600fn3">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>We highly approve your decision to go on with <gloss target="#t_Avalanche1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Avalanche</hi>
                    </gloss> and to land an airborne division near Rome on the conditions indicated.
                    We <pb facs="1376" n="1262" xml:id="pg_1262"/> fully recognize that military
                    consideration[s] must be dominant at this juncture.<note n="4" xml:id="d600fn4"
                        >A handwritten draft of this message, signed by Roosevelt and Churchill, is
                        in the Roosevelt Papers.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
